    "version": "0.1.0-manufactured-2026-05-13",
    "summary": "MEDITECH Greenfield publicly documents US Core STU7 patient health APIs based on FHIR R4 for patient, appointment, clinical, document, medication, device, and group-export retrieval workflows.",
    "description": "Manufactured OpenAPI artifact for MEDITECH Greenfield / FHIR APIs. This file was synthesized by Last Mile from curated research JSON and is not vendor-certified. Use it as an agent-consumable starting point, then validate paths, schemas, authentication, and server URLs with the vendor before production use. MEDITECH's public Greenfield documentation describes patient health data APIs designed to satisfy USCDI v3 requirements using HL7 FHIR US Core STU7 on top of FHIR R4. The public path listing shows resources such as AllergyIntolerance, Appointment, Binary, CarePlan, CareTeam, Communication, Condition, Coverage, Device, DiagnosticReport, DocumentReference, Encounter, Goal, Group, Immunization, Location, Medication, MedicationDispense, MedicationRequest, Observation, Organization, Patient, Practitioner, Procedure, QuestionnaireResponse, RelatedPerson, ServiceRequest, Specimen, and Task under the v2/uscore/STU7 namespace, plus group operations and patient-specific operations. The documentation emphasizes OAuth 2.0, OpenID Connect, institution-managed application configuration, and patient linking, but does not show public write-capable operations for this surface. Asset data is Unsupported. Telemetry data is Unsupported. Writeback is Unsupported.",
